sec.p:
All 32 in-patient units accredited on the Quality Network for Eating Disorders (QED) in the UK were contacted via email, using an electronic survey (Supplementary Appendix 1 available at https://doi.org/10.1192/bjb.2018.51). The individuals contacted were those registered on the QED network and included consultant psychiatrists, psychologists, senior nurses and occupational therapists. The survey for the professionals asked for feedback on three themes: (1)
if they were a single or mixed gender unit and how they arranged the ward to accommodate both genders;(2)
if the trust, commissioners or the CQC had ever commented on or stopped admission of male patients;(3)
if the professional had any views on recovery of patients in same or mixed gender environments.
